Hi!
> > Are there any patches which make userspace
> > filesystems (translators) under Linux available ?
> 
> Additionnally to CODA (that I really should look into some day ...),
> there is:
> 
>    - userfs: real (slow, but allows easy code prototyping) user-space
>              filesystems
> 
>    - FIST: (portable) stackable filesystem, however in kernel mode.
> 
>    - podfuk (haven't looked into this one yet)
Podfuk is based on coda, and it shows coda is actually nice to
use. See 
http://atrey.karlin.mff.cuni.cz/~pavel/podfuk/podfuk.html
>    - the perl interface InterMezzo uses (
http://www.InterMezzo.org
 or
